The paper deals with the problem of temporal action localization in videos, which involves analyzing and understanding the content of videos. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for this task, which involves training a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to optimize a structured objective. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Furthermore, the paper involves processing and analyzing multimedia data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves developing an algorithmic solution for a specific problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
